                           <locus target="#1rb">Fols. 1rb-2</locus>va: Excerpts from Zǝmmare.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The excerpts are very crudely written in a secondary hand.
They are adduced from Zǝmmare zä-Däbrä Zäyt (fols. 1r-1v; the proper order is 1v-1r) and from Zǝmmare zä-Niqodimos (fols. 2r-2v).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Tämälläs-signs indicating the place where omissions, written in the margins, belong:&#xD;
Fols. 5ra l.3, 5rb l.12, 6rb l.13, 6va l.24, 6vb l.14, 10ra l.23, 11rb l.8, 12rb l.17, 20ra l.2, 51rb l.19, 55va l.2, 59rb l.18, 79rb l.3: tämälläs-signs in the shape of a cross, in the main hand.&#xD;
Fols. 8ra l.6, 8va l.4, 27ra l.5, 42rb l.12, 49vb l.11, 60ra l.16: tämälläs-signs in the shape of a cross with circles at the end of the arms, in a secondary hand. &#xD;
Fol. 45vb l.10: tämälläs-signs in the shape of two perpendicular lines, in a secondary hand.&#xD;
- Pen trial: fol 1r.&#xD;
- Writing exercises, crude drawings, doodles; in pen and pencil: fols. 1r, 2v, 82rb, 89r, 89v.</item>
                     </list>
